  Docsplit is a command-line utility and Ruby client for splitting apart
  documents into their component parts: pages as plain UTF-8 text for 
  search indexing, images or thumbnails in any format, single-page PDFs,
  and document metadata (title, author, number of pages...)
  
  Installation:
  gem install docsplit
  
  For documentation, usage, and examples, see:
  http://documentcloud.github.com/docsplit/
  
  To suggest a feature or report a bug: 
  http://github.com/documentcloud/docsplit/issues/

